SUMMARY:Olio Read-in: Kafka's Metamorphosis
DESCRIPTION:"As Gregor Samsa awoke one morning from uneasy dreams he found 
 himself transformed in his bed into a gigantic insect." The enigmatic open
 ing sentence of Kafka's Metamorphosis has been perplexing translators\, in
 spiring illustrators\, and intriguing psychiatrists for over a century. Wh
 at kind of bug is Gregor? Is his transformation a process or a freak accid
 ent? Does his metamorphosis symbolize coming out? Or perils of capitalism?
  Anticipation of fascism? Body dysmorphia? Bad faith? Disability? Marginal
 ity?In this Olio Read-in\, we will be performing a close reading of Part 1
  of Metamorphosis. By focusing on minuscule details — linguistic choices
 \, floor plans\, food crumbs — we will enter Kafka's nightmarish univers
 e that is strikingly similar to our own.Rooted in the social revolution of
  the 1960s\, Read-ins have always been essential to the political project 
 of building communities\, and bolstering progressive change. Read Ins anno
 unce: We will not remain alone\, afraid\, and cut off from one another. No
 . We will sit side by side and with the support of each other\, we will re
 ad. We will learn. We will enrich our inner world so that we can find the 
 courage to exist outside of it.Teacher: Dina Odnopozova Dina Odnopozova ho
 lds a PhD from Yale and is a professor at Baruch College\, where her work 
 explores the intersection of literature\, psychology\, and the unconscious
 . She has led Olios on Freud\, Jung\, and the archetypal grammar of fairy 
 tales — the witches\, wolves\, and forbidden doors that map the human su
 bconscious. In this Read-in\, she brings that same depth of attention to K
 afka.What Is an Olio? Think Olio is an ongoing experiment in lifelong lear
 ning. We are a community of open-minded people who gather to exchange idea
 s with new friends and connect over art\, literature\, and philosophy. Che
 ck out our full calendar Our $30 membership gives you two events for the p
 rice of one!An Olio is what we call the social learning events we've been 
 organizing since 2015. A blend between a lecture and a house party\, Olios
  are led by a teacher who loves sharing their passions and the room is fil
 led with curious\, open-minded New Yorkers.Our goal is to spark new perspe
 ctives\, ignite curiosity\, and enjoy ourselves socially—an alternative 
 to typical nightlife options.Disclaimer: By purchasing a ticket\, you agre
 e to have your photo/video used for social media/marketing materials. If y
 ou prefer to not have your photo taken\, feel free to send us a note. Phot
 o by Zhi-Da Zhong\n\nTickets & info: https://www.viewcy.com/event/olio_rea
 din_kafkas
URL:https://www.viewcy.com/event/olio_readin_kafkas
END:VEVENT
