SUMMARY:EAVESDROPPING: The Erotics of Listening
DESCRIPTION:Why does overhearing feel so intimate?This Olio explores the st
 range emotional and psychological pleasure of listening to conversations n
 ot meant for us. Moving through the worlds of cinema\, opera\, sound art\,
  and everyday life\, artist/composer Whitney George examines how listening
  can become a form of desire\, fantasy\, suspense\, voyeurism\, and partic
 ipation — and why fragmented or partial speech often feels more seductiv
 e than direct access. Part lecture\, part listening session\, and part cul
 tural séance\, The Erotics of Listening asks why voices heard through wal
 ls\, telephones\, recordings\, and overheard moments continue to fascinate
  us — and what it means to find ourselves emotionally drawn toward priva
 te worlds we were never invited into.Whitney George is a composer\, conduc
 tor\, and interdisciplinary artist whose work moves between tragedy and ec
 stasy\, intimacy and the macabre. Her music is haunted by ghosts and love 
 — exploring irrationality\, nightmare\, and memory\, and sonically seeki
 ng lost objects and hidden subjects.Across installation\, stage\, and film
 \, she builds environments to be inhabited rather than watched: 1919 New O
 rleans under a serial killer's shadow\, a 1920s speakeasy in literary Harl
 em\, a Chinatown family inside the 1900 Bubonic Plague. She is the artisti
 c director and conductor of The Curiosity Cabinet\, the ensemble she has l
 ed since 2009\, and her recordings appear on Pinch Records.She holds a BFA
  from CalArts\, an MM from Brooklyn College\, and a DMA from the CUNY Grad
 uate Center. She is on faculty at Luna Lab and teaches composition private
 ly in Brooklyn.Evening Flow7 PM – Doors open. Settle in\, grab a drink\,
  and meet a friend.8 PM – The Olio begins: an intimate\, interactive lec
 ture and guided exploration.9 PM – We shift into a social experience\, d
 iscussing ideas with others in the room while the teacher joins and floats
  between conversations.10 PM - Last call at the bar and we'll start to win
 d down the evening.What Is an Olio?Think Olio is an ongoing experiment in 
 lifelong learning. We are a community of open-minded people who gather to 
 exchange ideas with new friends and connect over art\, literature\, and ph
 ilosophy.Check out our full calendarOur $30 membership gives you two event
 s for the price of one!&nbsp\;An Olio is what we call the social learning 
 events we’ve been organizing since 2015. A blend between a lecture and a
  house party\, Olios are led by a teacher who loves sharing their passions
  and the room is filled with curious\, open-minded New Yorkers.&nbsp\;Our 
 goal is to spark new perspectives\, ignite curiosity\, and enjoy ourselves
  socially—an alternative to typical nightlife options.Disclaimer: By pur
 chasing a ticket\, you agree to have your photo/video used for social medi
 a/marketing materials. If you prefer to not have your photo taken\, feel f
 ree to send us a note.Photo by Zhi-Da Zhong\n\nTickets & info: https://www
 .viewcy.com/event/eavesdropping_the_er
